  "strategy": [
    "Prioritize moving toward the marker as soon as marker_seen is detected.",
    "Use commit states for all primary controllable actions to avoid oscillations and ensure action completion.",
    "After each forward commit or recovery, insert a scan (full_rotate) to search for the marker and avoid long straight runs.",
    "Use recovery states after obstacle detection to prevent immediate return to forward movement and ensure safe escape.",
    "When marker_close is detected, transition to a stop state to safely complete the task.",
    "If the marker is lost, resume scanning/exploration rather than returning to forward movement.",
    "Never allow move_forward in response to obstacle_front; always use recovery or scan first.",
    "Avoid providing both clockwise and counterclockwise rotations in the same state.",
    "Alternate between forward and scan actions during exploration to maximize marker detection probability."
  ]
